[  20.23s] verdict: Daubechies wavelet basis is mathematically the WRONG direction for an LB on C_{1a}: restricting f to a finite-dim wavelet subspace gives val_W >= C_{1a} (an UPPER bound, smaller subspace = larger inf), and Shor relaxation of val_W gives only a LB on val_W itself, not on C_{1a}.  No analog of CS Lemma 1 (windowed test-value inequality) exists for wavelet coefficients that would connect the LB to C_{1a} universally.
